@node sect0 "Name"
xmp - Extended Module Player 


@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
@{b}xmp@{ub} [@{b}-a, --amplify@{ub} @{i}factor@{ui}] [@{b}-b, --bits@{ub} @{i}bits@{ui}] [@{b}-c, --stdout@{ub}] [@{b}-D@{ub} @{i}device-specific parameters@{ui}] [@{b}-d, --driver@{ub} @{i}driver@{ui}] [@{b}--fix-sample-loop@{ub}] [@{b}-f, --frequency@{ub} @{i}rate@{ui}] [@{b}-h, --help@{ub}] [@{b}-I, --instrument-path@{ub}] [@{b}-i, --info@{ub}] [@{b}-l, --loop@{ub}] [@{b}-M, --mute@{ub} @{i}channel-list@{ui}] [@{b}-m, --mono@{ub}] [@{b}--nocmd@{ub}] [@{b}-o, --output-file@{ub} @{i}filename@{ui}] [@{b}-P, --pan@{ub} @{i}pan@{ui}] [@{b}--probe-only@{ub}] [@{b}-R --random@{ub}] [@{b}-S, --solo@{ub} @{i}channel-list@{ui}] [@{b}-s, --start@{ub} @{i}pos@{ui}] [@{b}-t, --time@{ub} @{i}time@{ui}] [@{b}-u, --unsigned@{ub}] [@{b}-V, --version@{ub}] [@{b}-v, --verbose@{ub}] @{i}modules@{ui} 


@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
@{b}xmp@{ub} is a tracked music module player. It plays many module formats including Fasttracker II (XM), Noise/Fast/Protracker (MOD), Scream Tracker 3 (S3M) and Impulse Tracker (IT). Use CWxmp --help for a complete list of supported formats. @{b}xmp@{ub} can play through several output devices including the Open Sound System sequencer, linear and ulaw PCM audio devices or mixing to a raw or WAV file. 




@endnode

@node sect3 "Options"


À @{b}-a, --amplify@{ub} @{i}factor@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Amplification factor for the software mixer. Valid amplification factors range from 0 to 3. Default is 1. . Warning: higher amplification factors may cause distorted or noisy output. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-b, --bits@{ub} @{i}bits@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the software mixer resolution (8 or 16 bits). If ommited, The audio device will be opened at the highest resolution available. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-c, --stdout@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Mix the module to stdout. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-D@{ub} @{i}device-specific parameter@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Pass a configuration parameter to the device driver. See the @{b}DEVICE DRIVER PARAMETERS@{ub} section below for a list of known parameters.  @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-d, --driver@{ub} @{i}driver@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Select the output driver. If not specified, @{b}xmp@{ub} will try to probe each available driver. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}--fix-sample-loop@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Force sample loop start in samples instead of 16-bit words. This option affects only MOD files. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-f, --frequency@{ub} @{i}rate@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the software mixer sampling rate in hertz. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-h, --help@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Show a short summary of command-line options. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-I, --instrument-path@{ub} @{i}path@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the pathname to the directory containing external samples. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-i, --info@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Display module information and exit. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-l, --loop@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Enable module looping. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-M, --mute@{ub} @{i}channel-list@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Mute the specified channels. @{i}channel-list@{ui} is a comma-separated list of decimal channel ranges. Example: 0,2-4,8-16. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-m, --mono@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Force mono output (default is stereo in stereo-capable devices). @{lindent 0}

À @{b}--nocmd@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Disable interactive commands. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-o, --output-file@{ub} @{i}filename@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the output file name when mixing to raw or WAV files. If '-' is given as the file name, the output will be sent to stdout. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-P, --pan@{ub} @{i}num@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the percentual panning amplitude. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}--probe-only@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Exit after probing the audio device. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-R, --random@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Play modules in random order. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-S, --solo@{ub} @{i}channel-list@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Play only the specified channels. @{i}channel-list@{ui} is a comma-separated list of decimal channel ranges. Example: 0,2-4,8-16. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-s, --start@{ub} @{i}pos@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Start playing the module from the position @{i}pos@{ui}. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-t, --time@{ub} @{i}time@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Specifies the maximum playing time to @{i}time@{ui} seconds. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-u, --unsigned@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Tell the software mixer to use unsigned samples when mixing to a file (default is signed). @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-V, --version@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Print version information. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-v, --verbose@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Verbose mode (incremental). If specified more than once, the verbosity level will be increased (no messages will be displayed when the player runs in background). @{lindent 0}




@endnode

@node sect4 "Device Driver Parameters"
Use the option @{b}-D@{ub} to send parameters directly to the device drivers. Multiple @{b}-D@{ub} options can be specified in the command line. OSS software mixing: 



À @{b}-D@{ub} @{i}frag=num,size@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the maximum number of fragments to @{i}num@{ui} and the size of each fragment to @{i}size@{ui} bytes (must be a power of two). The number and size of fragments set a tradeoff between the buffering latency and sensibility to system load. To get better synchronization, reduce the values. To avoid gaps in the sound playback, increase the values. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-D@{ub} @{i}dev=device_name@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the audio device to open. Default is /dev/dsp. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-D@{ub} @{i}nosync@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Don't sync the OSS audio device between modules. @{lindent 0}

HP-UX and Solaris audio: 



À @{b}-D@{ub} @{i}gain=value@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the audio gain. Valid @{i}value@{ui} goes from 0 to 255. The default is 128. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-D@{ub} @{i}port={s|h|l}@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the audio port. Valid arguments are @{i}s@{ui} for the internal speaker, @{i}h@{ui} for headphones and @{i}l@{ui} for line out. The default is the internal speaker. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-D@{ub} @{i}buffer=size@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Set the size in bytes of the audio buffer. The default value is 32 Kb. @{lindent 0}

File output: 



À @{b}-D@{ub} @{i}endian=big@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Generate big-endian 16-bit samples (default is the machine byte ordering). @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-D@{ub} @{i}endian=little@{ui}@{lindent 3}
Generate little-endian 16-bit samples (default is the machine byte ordering). @{lindent 0}




@endnode

@node sect5 "Interactive Commands"
The following single key commands can be used when playing modules: 

À @{b}q, Esc@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Stop the currently playing module and quit the player. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}f, Right@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Jump to the next pattern. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}b, Left@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Jump to the previous pattern. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}n, Up@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Jump to the next module. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}p, Down@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Jump to the previous module. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}Space@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Pause or unpause module replay. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}1@{ub}, @{b}2@{ub}, @{b}3@{ub}, @{b}4@{ub}, @{b}5@{ub}, @{b}6@{ub}, @{b}7@{ub}, @{b}8@{ub}, @{b}9@{ub}, @{b}0@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Mute/unmute channels 1 to 10. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}!@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Unmute all channels. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}?@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Display available commands. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}m@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Display module information. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}i@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Display combined instrument/sample list. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}I@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Display instrument list. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}S@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Display sample list. @{lindent 0}

Interactive mode can be disabled using the @{b}--nocmd@{ub} command line option. 




@endnode

@node sect6 "Notes"
When using the OSS sequencer with an AWE card, xmp will wipe out any soundfonts already loaded in the card. 


@endnode

@node sect7 "Examples"
Play module muting channels 0 to 3 and 6: 

À CWxmp --mute=0-3,6 module.mod.gz @{lindent 3}
@{lindent 0}

Play modules in /dev/dsp using the default device settings (unsigned 8bit, 8 kHz mono): 



À CWxmp -o/dev/dsp -f8000 -m -b8 -u module.lha @{lindent 3}
@{lindent 0}

Play all XM modules in the /mod directory and all subdirectories in random order: 



À CWxmp -R `find /mod -name "*.xm*" -print` @{lindent 3}
@{lindent 0}




@endnode

@node sect8 "Environment"


À @{b}XMP_INSTRUMENT_PATH@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Pathname to directory containing samples if not contained in the module. @{lindent 0}





À @{b}XMP_MED2_INSTRUMENT_PATH@{ub}@{lindent 3}
Overrides samples directory for the MED2 loader. @{lindent 0}




@endnode

@node sect9 "Files"
CW/etc/xmp/xmp.conf, $HOME/.xmp/xmp.conf, /etc/xmp/modules.conf, $HOME/.xmp/modules.conf 


@endnode

